House and Senate who don't like
to see the
federal government spending
money on roads,

18:09.155 --> 18:12.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
even though that is usually what
we have done
throughout the past.

18:12.992 --> 18:13.960 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And he said, "I know."

18:13.993 --> 18:15.761 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
So, we will see.

18:15.795 --> 18:18.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We have heard
different things
from different people around
President Trump

18:18.864 --> 18:20.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about what they want to do about
tax cuts.

18:20.866 --> 18:22.268 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do you think they're going
to do?

18:22.301 --> 18:23.502 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do you have a clear idea?

18:23.536 --> 18:25.304 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

18:25.338 --> 18:27.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Yes, I really
worry, again,
because he's governing from the
hard right,

18:27.940 --> 18:32.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that the overwhelming part of
their tax cuts
will go to the wealthiest of
Americans.

18:32.478 --> 18:37.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's been the credo of the
hard right all
along, reduce taxes on the very
rich, and

18:37.350 --> 18:38.651 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it will trickle down.

18:38.684 --> 18:41.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's not something Democrats
or most Americans
agree with.

18:41.654 --> 18:46.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I don't think he would get
very much support
for tax cuts that predominantly
go to the

18:46.726 --> 18:48.060 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
top 1 percent.

18:48.094 --> 18:50.096 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It would be against what he
campaigned on.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.564 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It would be a huge mistake.

18:51.597 --> 18:52.732 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's not the way to do things.

18:52.765 --> 18:55.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, middle-class tax cuts, we
would look at
them.

18:55.968 --> 18:59.372 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Closing loopholes, he has talked
about closing
the carried interest loophole.

18:59.405 --> 19:01.574 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We would be all for it and vote
for that.

19:01.607 --> 19:02.908 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we will see what he does.

19:02.942 --> 19:05.978 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Russia and Russia
sanctions.

19:06.012 --> 19:11.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Whatever is decided by Congress
in terms of
continuing or amping up
retaliatory moves

19:11.183 --> 19:17.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
against Russia for its role in
the election,
isn't it likely that the
Republican majority

19:17.723 --> 19:20.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the Senate is going to not go
along with
that; basically, that it won't
go anywhere?

19:20.960 --> 19:22.795 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

19:22.828 --> 19:26.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Well, our
Republican colleagues,
their credo since the days of
Ronald Reagan

19:26.332 --> 19:31.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
would be to be tough on Putin
and Russia,
would be to increase sanctions
if they did

19:31.303 --> 19:33.039 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
this.

19:33.072 --> 19:35.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I hope that they will --
John McCain and
Lindsey Graham, to their credit,
have been

19:35.341 --> 19:38.010 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stuck with this, a few others,
Ben Sasse.

19:38.044 --> 19:42.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But most seem to be, just
whatever Donald
Trump wants on foreign policy,
they are going

19:42.481 --> 19:43.449 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to do.

19:43.482 --> 19:44.583 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have abandoned their
beliefs.

19:44.617 --> 19:46.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think they're going to pay
a price for
that.

19:46.585 --> 19:50.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We, the country, will a pay a
price substantively,
and they will pay a price
politically.

19:50.790 --> 19:57.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Quite a
remarkable display
of public, strong feelings in
that march on

19:57.396 --> 19:58.364 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Saturday.

19:58.397 --> 19:59.365 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

19:59.398 --> 20:00.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:00.666 --> 20:01.367 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: I was at the New
York for three-and-a-half-hours.

20:01.400 --> 20:03.235 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was exhilarating.

20:03.269 --> 20:04.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Many people say
they haven't
seen in a long time from the
Democratic Party.

20:04.537 --> 20:05.504 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:05.538 --> 20:06.705 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Yes.

20:06.739 --> 20:07.506 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But where do
Democrats go from
here?

20:07.540 --> 20:08.474 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:08.507 --> 20:09.475 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHUCK SCHUMER: OK.

20:09.508 --> 20:10.476 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That was one day.

20:10.509 --> 20:11.477 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:11.510 --> 20:12.478 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Yes.

20:12.511 --> 20:13.479 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Where do you go
from here?

20:13.512 --> 20:15.381 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:15.414 --> 20:17.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Well, but to say
on the second
day, there should be a whole
plan and everyone

20:17.249 --> 20:17.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is going to be marching to the
polls in 2018,
which would be the right thing
to do, is a

20:17.750 --> 20:19.452 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
little premature.

20:19.485 --> 20:24.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the fact that there is such
a depth of
feeling and worry about this new
president,

20:24.390 --> 20:29.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the fact that women feel on the
issues of
choice and on the issues of
Planned Parenthood

20:29.929 --> 20:35.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and even on the issues of the
Affordable Care
Act, which say women have to be
treated equally

20:35.134 --> 20:38.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to men, that he's not working
for them, that's
going to have a huge effect.

20:38.838 --> 20:44.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that's going to help
us over the
-- not just in the elections in
2018 and 2020,

20:44.243 --> 20:46.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but over the next several
months.

20:46.045 --> 20:49.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do you make
sure both that
you stand up for what you
believe in, but

20:49.315 --> 20:53.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you don't come across to the
American people
as just a battering ram of no,
no, no?

20:53.853 --> 20:54.820 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:54.854 --> 20:55.921 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: That's exactly...

20:55.955 --> 20:56.822 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And including on
these confirmations?

20:56.856 --> 20:57.857 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:57.890 --> 20:58.824 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: It's a very
important question.

20:58.858 --> 20:59.825 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Stick to our values.

20:59.859 --> 21:01.093 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
OK?

21:01.127 --> 21:03.796 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you stick to your values,
then you will
be guided right.

21:03.829 --> 21:05.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's what I have always done
throughout
my career.

21:05.664 --> 21:09.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we're not going to oppose
something because
the name Trump is on it just for
the sake

21:09.368 --> 21:11.737 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of opposition, as Mitch
McConnell did.

21:11.770 --> 21:15.841 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
If he proposes a good
infrastructure plan
that meets our values, we will
work with him

21:15.875 --> 21:17.510 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on it.

21:17.543 --> 21:20.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If he wants to change the trade
laws in a
real way, we will work with him
on it.

21:20.312 --> 21:26.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, at the same time, when he
tries to roll
over our values, repeal the
protections we

21:26.285 --> 21:31.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
put for consumers and the
country against
Wall Street, repeal clean air
and clean water,

21:31.991 --> 21:37.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
repeal health care and the ACA,
undo the help
and support we have given public
education,

21:37.897 --> 21:39.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we will fight him tooth and
nail.

21:39.865 --> 21:42.034 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that's what the
country wants
us to do.

21:42.067 --> 21:45.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senate Minority
Leader Chuck
Schumer, thank you very much.

21:45.371 --> 21:46.338 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:46.372 --> 21:48.174 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Nice to see you.

21:48.207 --> 21:51.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And in one final
postscript,
after we were done, I asked the
minority leader

21:51.043 --> 21:53.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about his personal relationship
with President
Trump.

21:53.946 --> 21:55.381 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:55.414 --> 21:58.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: He was saying to
me he was
my friend at the beginning.

21:58.083 --> 21:59.752 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Then he called me some names.

21:59.785 --> 22:04.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what I have said is, either
isn't going
to affect me.

22:04.723 --> 22:06.592 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Flattering isn't going to affect
me.

22:06.625 --> 22:08.127 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Name-calling isn't going to
affect me.

22:08.160 --> 22:11.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm going to go by what is the
right thing
to do in terms of our values.

22:11.230 --> 22:16.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, I think both Democrats and
Republicans
have a lot of question marks
about his operating

22:16.101 --> 22:18.404 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
style.

22:18.437 --> 22:23.075 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm worried.

22:23.108 --> 22:34.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we said
earlier, there's
been plenty of news in the past
24 hours about

22:34.153 --> 22:36.689 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
President Trump and his
businesses.

22:36.722 --> 22:42.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, there are continuing
questions about
his pledge to separate from his
businesses

22:42.061 --> 22:43.762 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
now that he's in the White
House.

22:43.796 --> 22:45.598 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham is here with
more.

22:45.631 --> 22:49.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That federal
lawsuit that
was filed earlier today alleges
that President

22:49.335 --> 22:53.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Trump is violating the
Emoluments Clause of
the Constitution.

22:53.472 --> 22:57.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That clause bars government
officials from
receiving certain types of gifts
from foreign

22:57.643 --> 22:59.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
powers or governments.

22:59.245 --> 23:02.982 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As we heard, the president
called the suit
totally without merit.

23:03.015 --> 23:07.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In other developments, White
House spokesman
Sean Spicer said today the
president had resigned

23:07.920 --> 23:10.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from his businesses in full, as
he'd promised
to do.

23:10.489 --> 23:14.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There have been questions as to
whether that
had indeed happened, but, late
today, several

23:14.960 --> 23:20.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
news organizations said they had
received
signed letters and filings
showing the process

23:20.399 --> 23:22.334 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
had indeed begun.

23:22.368 --> 23:25.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jonathan O'Connell is covering
all this for
The Washington Post, and he
joins me now.

23:25.904 --> 23:29.208 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Jonathan, let's start
specifically with this
lawsuit.

23:29.241 --> 23:31.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What is the argument that these
plaintiffs
are arguing?

23:31.343 --> 23:33.178 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JONATHAN O'CONNELL, The
Washington Post: Sure.

23:33.212 --> 23:37.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What they're taking aim at is
the Emoluments
Clause of the Constitution, as
you mentioned.

23:37.383 --> 23:42.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's an obscure clause that
really no one
had paid much attention to until
recently.

23:42.855 --> 23:48.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What it does is, it bars the
president and
other federal officials from
receiving benefits

23:48.460 --> 23:52.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of any kind from foreign leaders
or foreign
officials.

23:52.798 --> 23:59.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, unfortunately, there isn't
a lot of case
record in terms of courts really
breaking

23:59.171 --> 24:02.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that apart and explaining what
that might
mean, and the Supreme Court has
never addressed

24:02.641 --> 24:04.443 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it.

24:04.476 --> 24:10.049 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, there is a wide view of
opinions on what
an emolument might mean, what
might qualify

24:10.082 --> 24:16.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as an emolument, and also what
might qualify
as a violation of the Emoluments
Clause.

24:16.355 --> 24:22.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People are talking about some of
the businesses
that Mr. Trump has that receive
payments from

24:22.861 --> 24:28.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
federal officials or foreign
governments,
or have -- receive interest
payments from

24:29.001 --> 24:31.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
maybe foreign banks.

24:31.203 --> 24:33.672 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are foreign buyers of his
condominiums.

24:33.706 --> 24:37.876 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are foreign tenants or
foreign-owned
tenants of his buildings.

24:37.910 --> 24:42.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Mr. Trump is trying to take
precautions
to separate himself from his
businesses as

24:42.348 --> 24:44.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
much as he can, but retain
ownership of them.

24:44.717 --> 24:47.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Help me
understand what
the concern is here.

24:47.820 --> 24:53.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is it that, if I'm a foreign
government and
I am somehow putting money into
a Trump-related

24:53.392 --> 24:57.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
organization, that that might
somehow curry
favor with the president?

24:57.996 --> 24:59.865 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JONATHAN O'CONNELL: Sure.

24:59.898 --> 25:04.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yes, the original idea was to
avoid bribery
from occurring and make sure
that the president

25:04.770 --> 25:08.874 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and other officials were focused
on doing
the best thing for the nation.

25:08.907 --> 25:15.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that core ideal is, I think,
at the center
of this initial lawsuit and the
other lawsuits

25:15.280 --> 25:20.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that could be to come, which is
out of a concern
that Mr. Trump will continue to
have some

25:20.252 --> 25:24.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
allegiance to his businesses,
because he does
still own them and he would
still benefit

25:24.723 --> 25:29.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or profit from their doing well
at the same
time as he is president.

25:29.328 --> 25:35.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there -- you know, he just
has -- he has
such a wide array of businesses
that he started,

25:35.300 --> 25:38.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to think about all the various
conflicts that
he could have in the various
parts of the

25:38.837 --> 25:42.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
federal government that he will
oversee, it
is going to take quite a bit of
unwinding.

25:42.941 --> 25:47.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: China is one
of the examples
that is often cited when we talk
about this

25:47.613 --> 25:48.580 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
clause.

25:48.614 --> 25:50.149 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
China rents space in Trump
Tower.

25:50.182 --> 25:52.050 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JONATHAN O'CONNELL: Sure.

25:52.084 --> 25:54.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: A Chinese
government bank,
I know, loans money for a
Trump-related project.

25:55.020 --> 25:59.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What is it that the people who
are bringing
the suit want the Trump
Organization to do?

25:59.892 --> 26:05.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN O'CONNELL: I think
there is a couple
different motives for a suit
like this.

26:05.130 --> 26:10.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One is, if you can get far
enough along down
the line in a lawsuit, you can
get to the

26:10.469 --> 26:13.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
discovery phase, as any attorney
would know,
and that's when you sort of get
to learn much

26:13.772 --> 26:17.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
more about what the opposing
party has at
stake here.

26:17.643 --> 26:21.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then, you know, maybe they
can unearth
some of Mr. Trump's financials.

26:21.480 --> 26:24.416 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Maybe they could even unearth
his tax returns.

26:24.450 --> 26:27.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some of this might be a long
