down to 11 percent.

46:40.331 --> 46:44.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the reason for that appears
to be that
Chancellor Merkel's government
has promised

46:44.368 --> 46:49.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a new raft of security measures,
including
the fast deportation of criminal
refugees

46:49.974 --> 46:52.543 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and migrants.

46:52.576 --> 46:57.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Providing more workers for
Germany's powerhouse
economy was one of Merkel's
justifications

46:57.148 --> 47:00.284 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for her open door immigration
policy.

47:00.317 --> 47:04.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With elections looming this
autumn, Merkel's
Christian Democratic Union is
perceived as

47:04.889 --> 47:11.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
having a steadier hand on the
tiller of prosperity
than the untested AFD, or
Alternative for

47:11.362 --> 47:13.264 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Germany Party.

47:13.297 --> 47:19.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At Koblenz's biggest monument,
the AFD's alleged
Nazi tendencies were satirized
with cardboard

47:19.170 --> 47:22.606 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
cutouts of Second World War
dictators.

47:22.640 --> 47:26.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That impression was reinforced
after one of
its senior members said that
Germany should

47:26.911 --> 47:31.348 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
abandon what he called its
shameful memories
about the Holocaust.

47:31.382 --> 47:36.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This might explain the subdued
speech of party
leader Frauke Petry on the banks
of the Rhine.

47:36.520 --> 47:43.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRAUKE PETRY, Chair, Alternative
for Germany
Party (through translator): We
have to expose

47:43.427 --> 47:49.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
those who call for a more
powerful European
Union as the true
anti-Europeans, the true

47:49.967 --> 47:52.036 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
anti-democrats.

47:52.069 --> 47:55.740 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have an answer to these
spineless technocrats.

47:55.773 --> 48:00.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that answer is people and
politicians
who are going to take back
Europe and restore

48:00.978 --> 48:02.747 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
its freedom and sovereignty.

48:02.780 --> 48:07.251 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The
right-wingers may be
hoping to benefit from the Trump
effect, but,

48:07.284 --> 48:13.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on Inauguration Day, most
customers in this
cafe were turning a blind eye.

48:13.624 --> 48:17.595 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Koblenz gathering generated
two days of
protests.

48:17.628 --> 48:19.363 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
History student Anna Khodorova:

48:19.396 --> 48:25.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANNA KHODOROVA, Student: It kind
of reminds
me of the time when Hitler was
still alive,

48:25.736 --> 48:34.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because he used populism against
Jews, against
other discriminated groups of
people.

48:34.311 --> 48:40.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have learned from history,
and I'm afraid
that this happens again also
when Trump becomes

48:40.050 --> 48:41.786 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
president.

48:41.819 --> 48:51.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The next day,
outside the
conference center, a band played
the anthem

48:51.695 --> 48:54.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the European Union, which the
nationalists
despise.

48:54.899 --> 49:00.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
English teacher Herman Spix
fears that Europe
is backsliding into the darkest
period of

49:00.571 --> 49:02.273 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
German history.

49:02.306 --> 49:07.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HERMAN SPIX, Teacher: I'm very,
very much
concerned, because I have been
working on

49:07.645 --> 49:13.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the issue of the Third Reich for
nearly 20
years.

49:13.083 --> 49:15.619 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is -- in my sense, it is
comparable.

49:15.653 --> 49:22.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: More and more people are
spreading
racism, sexism, and homophobe
sentiments or

49:22.960 --> 49:24.762 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
whatever.

49:24.795 --> 49:30.968 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
If they come into the
parliament, it will
be a big difference, because I
think we will

49:31.001 --> 49:36.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all be very astonished at what
they will do.

49:36.340 --> 49:41.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The police
erected a protective
ring around the conference
center.

49:41.645 --> 49:47.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Local AFD councillor Ulrich
Langenback rejected
accusations that they are Nazis
in suits.

49:47.451 --> 49:49.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ULRICH LANGENBACK, Councillor,
Alternative
for Germany Party: For me, they
are.

49:49.486 --> 49:51.422 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I will not use his word.

49:51.455 --> 49:55.059 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are the fascists, because
it's only young
people.

49:55.092 --> 49:58.729 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, they got brainwashed by
school and university.

49:58.762 --> 50:03.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Happy to
demonstrate their
enthusiasm in the dark, not so
many were prepared

50:03.968 --> 50:05.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to voice their opinions
publicly.

50:05.603 --> 50:07.338 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ULRICH LANGENBACK: Germany is
very weak.

50:07.371 --> 50:10.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You are not allowed to speak
openly.

50:10.074 --> 50:14.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're -- always when you speak
if you are
in the AFD, you can worry about
your job.

50:14.078 --> 50:18.549 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: These
nationalists hope that
hitching themselves to the Trump
bandwagon

50:18.582 --> 50:21.218 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will bring electoral success.

50:21.252 --> 50:25.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In order to symbolize unity,
they held their
conference where Germany's two
great rivers

50:26.023 --> 50:27.892 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
meet.

50:27.925 --> 50:31.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But their message emphasized
growing divisions
within Europe, as the continent
steams deeper

50:31.929 --> 50:34.064 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
into an unpredictable 2017.

50:34.098 --> 50:38.869 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Malcolm Brabant
in Koblenz.

50:38.903 --> 50:49.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to our
"NewsHour" Shares,
something that caught our eye
that might be

50:49.213 --> 50:51.081 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of interest to you, too.

50:51.115 --> 50:55.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every winter, millions of tons
of salt are
spread across the country's
roads and sidewalks.

50:55.886 --> 50:59.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Much of it comes Ohio's Whiskey
Island Salt
Mine.

50:59.823 --> 51:05.195 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Elizabeth Miller of WVIZ/PBS
ideastream in
Cleveland reports.

51:05.229 --> 51:11.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH MILLER: When old man
winter rears
his icy head, there's one thing
that keeps

51:11.101 --> 51:15.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ohio from becoming a virtual
slip 'n slide:
salt.

51:15.806 --> 51:21.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A natural deicer, over 17
million tons of
rock salt was spread over roads
and sidewalks

51:21.578 --> 51:25.983 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the United States during the
particularly
fierce winter of 2015.

51:26.016 --> 51:29.920 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But where does it all come from?

51:29.954 --> 51:31.622 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The answer might surprise you.

51:31.655 --> 51:37.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Right now, we are in the
Whiskey Island
Mine, 1,800 feet below Lake
Erie.

51:37.528 --> 51:41.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we are mining salt for the
purposes of
road deicing.

51:41.899 --> 51:47.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last year, we mined a little
over three million
tons in a pretty mild winter.

51:47.171 --> 51:52.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In a normal winter, we will do
about four
million tons a year.

51:52.977 --> 51:56.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH MILLER: Ohio is one of
the top exporters
of salt in the country, and it's
actually

51:56.647 --> 52:01.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mined right under our noses in
places like
Cargill's Whiskey Island Salt
Mine.

52:01.652 --> 52:05.889 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The 12-square-mile mine lies
just offshore
of downtown Cleveland.

52:05.923 --> 52:12.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Once we blast the salt out
of the ground,
we got ahead and scoop it up and
put it on

52:12.696 --> 52:16.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the belt lines to be sent to the
mill for
processing.

52:16.166 --> 52:21.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH MILLER: A system of
conveyor belts
and elevators bring the salt to
the surface.

52:21.238 --> 52:23.674 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Left behind are gigantic pillars
of salt.

52:23.707 --> 52:27.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These support the weight of the
thousands
of feet of rock and lake above
the mine.

52:27.911 --> 52:29.279 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
But wait.

52:29.313 --> 52:34.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How did all this salt get here,
almost 2,000
feet under Lake Erie?

52:34.084 --> 52:38.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To answer that question, we
headed to Cleveland's
Museum of Natural History to
talk to expert

52:38.689 --> 52:40.457 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Harvey Webster.

52:40.491 --> 52:41.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARVEY WEBSTER, Cleveland Museum
of Natural
History: We always think, you
know, Cleveland,

52:41.692 --> 52:43.427 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ohio, has always been north of
the equator.

52:43.460 --> 52:46.096 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's been in a temperate
location kind of
forever, right?

52:46.130 --> 52:47.831 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And the answer is no.

52:47.865 --> 52:53.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It turns out that North America,
like all
the other continents, has moved
across the

52:53.270 --> 52:55.039 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
planet.

52:55.072 --> 52:58.809 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And at the time of the Silurian,
400 million
years ago, Cleveland, Ohio,
would have been

52:58.842 --> 53:05.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about 1,000 miles south of the
equator, in
shallow, tropical conditions.

53:05.315 --> 53:11.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH MILLER: So, Ohio was
tropical, oh,
yes, and covered in a shallow
sea.

53:11.855 --> 53:16.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And its inhabitants are not the
kind of thing
you see strolling in downtown
Cleveland today.

53:16.760 --> 53:21.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Eventually, these tropical
conditions and
some overgrown coral reefs
caused the sea

53:21.598 --> 53:23.734 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to dry up, leaving the salt
behind.

53:23.767 --> 53:29.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARVEY WEBSTER: It would get
saltier and saltier
and saltier, until, finally, the
salt literally

53:29.473 --> 53:33.644 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
settles right out of that water,
and forms
rock salt.

53:33.677 --> 53:39.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this happened thousands,
tens of thousands
of times, and each time it
happened, it would

53:39.683 --> 53:42.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
add a new layer to the rock
column.

53:42.886 --> 53:47.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, if you went to the
Cargill mine, when
you look at the walls, you will
see these

53:47.591 --> 53:49.326 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
alternating bands.

53:49.359 --> 53:53.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Each one of those layers is like
a chapter
in the history of the world
right here in

53:53.730 --> 53:57.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Cleveland as it existed 400
million years
ago.

53:57.201 --> 54:01.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH MILLER: The salt mine
looks like
another world, and it really is
one.

54:01.672 --> 54:04.441 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the remains of world that
existed long
before man.

54:04.475 --> 54:08.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But even if you never get down
to the mine,
you will still see pieces of
this world scattered

54:08.879 --> 54:11.482 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on icy roads all winter long.

54:11.515 --> 54:14.685 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Elizabeth Miller
in Cleveland, Ohio.

54:14.718 --> 54:18.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And thank you,
Ohio, for your
salt.

54:18.088 --> 54:19.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's the "NewsHour" for
tonight.

54:19.590 --> 54:20.891 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

54:20.924 --> 54:32.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For all of us at the "PBS
NewsHour," thank
you, and good night.
